      <abstract>
        <p>Barrick Gold Corp acquires exploration properties in Tanzania and Peru wi</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>In a further consolidation among gold miners, the Barrick Gold Corporation of Toronto has acquired exploration properties in Tanzania and Peru with a friendly takeover of Pangea Goldfields Inc. for 204 million Canadian dollars, or $140 million. The cash offer of 7 Canadian dollars a share for Pangea, also based in Toronto, was 18 percent above Pangea's closing price on Thursday. Most of Barrick's mines are in North America, but it also has one in Peru and Pangea's Tanzanian property ''fits into our development program that is well under way in Tanzania,'' said Randall Oliphant, Barrick's president and chief executive.</p>
        <p>Timothy Pritchard</p>
      </block>
